python src/secretary.py
​```llama (local embeddings)
                    ├─ SQLite (conversation + fact storage)
                    ├─ Google APIs (Calendar, Gmail, Tasks)
                    └─ signal-cli (encrypted two-way messaging)
```

**What stays on your machine:** full conversation history, extracted facts, embeddings, diary entries, local notes, OAuth tokens.

**What goes to the API:** the current message, a system prompt, a small set of locally-selected relevant context snippets, and a sliding window of recent messages.

